The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for automated discovery of patterns in complex dynamical systems, specifically cellular automata. This falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). However, since the focus is on the use of machine learning algorithms, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories.
